    </figcaption>
  </figure>

<p>
They also describe what it means to be vulnerable means as 
being authentic
embracing discomfort
admitting mistakes
And to listening actively and openly
Working in this way creates collacollaberotive, creative, and successful teams.


</p>

    <figure>
    <div class="third">
      <img src="/images/posts/leadership-in-context/eight.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="the-possibilities-with-patterns - slide two">
